						               													<description>Squad Hammer Man to Man is an expansion for the Squad Hammer rules focusing on adding a bit more character:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Namely to let you play games where the units are individual figures rather than squads of troops.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Within this supplement you will find:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Advice and suggestions for handling single-figure units in conventional games, including combat and spotting rule adjustments and new rules for Officers (inspired by Trench Hammer).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    A collection of new options for games where every unit is a single figure, including new damage mechanics, tweaks to the combat systems and more cinematic action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Notes on melee-only characters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    A new melee initiative system.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Rules for Goons: Perfect for Imperial storm troopers, nazi thugs and other cannon fodder.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    A detailed injury table allowing characters to be stunned, knocked out or otherwise injured when they get shot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Detailed infiltration rules for stealth scenarios, adapted from FiveCore.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    A D20 table allowing you to add individual objectives to a character: Perfect for solo gamers and big club games alike.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    A system to gain experience, upgrade your heroes... and have them die horribly in battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Many of these options are also applicable to games of Trench Hammer, October Hammer or Winter Hammer especially those of you who are interested in something a bit more pulpy and cinematic.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
